    <note>Lu(9) Yijian [8100] When Zhao(1) Renzong [9004] (qv.) took personal control over the government, Yijian and Renzong planned to dismiss from positions of power partisans of Yang(2) Huangtaihou [4215], regent during the emperor's minority. He was allied with the adopted son of Yan(4) Chenghan [2067] (qv.), Yan(4) Wenying [4117] during this period. Yijian was Mengheng's [7054] son, Mengzheng's [8101] nephew, Jujian's [1300] cousin, Gongzhuo's [7304], Gongru's [1315], Gongzhu's [1314] and Gongbi's [1316] father, Xichun's [1304], Xiji's [1305], Xijie's [7303] and Xidao's [1306] grandfather, and Jiawen's [1294] and Haowen's [8099] great grandfather. Yijian was the son-in-law of Fufeng jun Ma(2) Liang [1349] and father-in-law of Wang(2) Yong [7091]. LU(9) Xichang [1303] and Xicui [1307] have the same generational name as his grandsons and grandnephews. Zhang Fangping, WJ, 36.1a-11b. CBD, 2, 1202-3.</note>
